title: SDSU's Christion Named Missouri Valley Newcomer Of The Week
text:
SDSU's Christion Named Missouri Valley Newcomer Of The Week POSTED: 10:48 AM CDT Oct 12, 2015 
Photo Dave Eggen/Inertia BROOKINGS, S.D. - 
SDSU quarterback Taryn Christion accounted for 320 yards of total offense in leading South Dakota State to a 24-7 victory over Indiana State in his collegiate debut on Oct. 10. More from KDLT Arizona To Establish New Bison Herd In Conservation Effort 
Starting in place of an injured Zach Lujan, Christion opened the scoring with a 10-yard touchdown run early in the second quarter, then threw his first career touchdown pass – a 34-yarder to Jake Wieneke – later in the quarter. 
For the game, Christion completed 15-of-24 passes for 221 yards and carried the ball 16 times for 99 yards. Copyright © 2015, KDLT. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
